.TH "pcie_aspm_enabled" 9 "pcie_aspm_enabled" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcie_aspm_enabled \- Check if PCIe ASPM has been enabled for a device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" pcie_aspm_enabled
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
Target device.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Relies on the upstream bridge's link_state being valid.  The link_state
is deallocated only when the last child of the bridge (i.e., \fIpdev\fP or a
sibling) is removed, and the caller should be holding a reference to
\fIpdev\fP, so this should be safe.
